cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.AL 

This paper deals with the problem of finding minimum dominating sets in unit disk graphs, which is a well-studied problem in the field of computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the problem has applications in wireless ad-hoc networks, which suggests cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves geometric representations of graphs, which points towards cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as a possible sub-category. The use of approximation algorithms and complexity analysis suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity) as other potential sub-categories.
